{
  "stem": "2004.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he was still-- even though he was-- he came to-- even though during the day he worked for the German army repairing their trucks, but at night, he was-- he was sleeping in that paper factory.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And being that his mother was there also, so they were still together.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he must've gotten permission for his mother to stay in that paper factory because he must have acquainted some of these Germans that he worked for.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they used their pull to let him bring his mother to that paper factory, that tar paper factory.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So sometimes-- coming back now to late December or early January of 1943, they decided they no longer need us in that lumber yard.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So one day, they loaded us up on trucks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they have transported us to a town further inland in Poland called Rzeszow.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Rzeszow.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Had a relatively large Jewish population, and they had a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we were brought into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Not only were we brought into the ghetto, but I think within a week, they also decided that they no longer needed Jews in the tar paper factory.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So they took the people from the tar paper factory, and they also brought them to the ghetto in Rzeszow.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Of course, once you're in the ghetto, you are now subject to the Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had their Jewish sort of I wouldn't call them exactly collaborators, but they were the Jewish ghetto administration, which in some cases they may have been collaborators.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In some cases, they may not have been collaborators.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But in my experience, many, many of those people that worked in that committee were really straightforward people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They tried to be fair, as fair as they could.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
